defs.docs: The code itself.

defs.docs: A line of code associated with the Diagnostic

defs.docs: The line of code associated with the error

defs.docs: Start of the section of the line to highlight. 1-based, character offset in self.text

defs.docs: End of the section of the line to highlight. 1-based, character offset in self.text

defs.name: DiagnosticSpanMacroExpansion
defs.docs: Macro expansion information associated with a diagnostic.

defs.name: span
defs.docs:
span where macro was applied to generate this code; note that
 this may itself derive from a macro (if
 `span.expansion.is_some()`)

defs.name: macro_decl_name
defs.docs: name of macro that was applied (e.g., "foo!" or "#[derive(Eq)]")

defs.name: def_site_span
defs.docs: span where macro was defined (if known)

defs.name: DiagnosticSpan
defs.value: DiagnosticSpan { file_name, byte_start, byte_end, line_start, line_end, column_start, column_end, is_primary, text, label, suggested_replacement, suggestion_applicability, expansion }
defs.docs: A section of the source code associated with a Diagnostic

defs.name: file_name
defs.docs: The file name this diagnostic comes from.

defs.name: byte_start
defs.docs: The byte offset in the file where this diagnostic starts from.

defs.name: byte_end
defs.docs: The byte offset in the file where this diagnostic ends.

defs.name: line_start
defs.docs: 1-based. The line in the file.

defs.name: line_end
defs.docs: 1-based. The line in the file.

defs.name: column_start
defs.docs: 1-based, character offset.

defs.name: column_end
defs.docs: 1-based, character offset.

defs.name: is_primary
defs.docs:
Is this a "primary" span -- meaning the point, or one of the points,
 where the error occurred?

defs.name: text
defs.docs: Source text from the start of line_start to the end of line_end.

defs.name: label
defs.docs: Label that should be placed at this location (if any)

defs.name: suggested_replacement
defs.docs:
If we are suggesting a replacement, this will contain text
 that should be sliced in atop this span.

defs.name: suggestion_applicability
defs.docs: If the suggestion is approximate

defs.name: expansion
defs.docs: Macro invocations that created the code at this span, if any.

defs.name: MachineApplicable
defs.docs: The suggested replacement can be applied automatically safely

defs.name: HasPlaceholders
defs.docs:
The suggested replacement has placeholders that will need to be manually
 replaced.

defs.name: MaybeIncorrect
defs.docs:
The suggested replacement may be incorrect in some circumstances. Needs
 human review.

defs.name: Unspecified
defs.docs: The suggested replacement will probably not work.

defs.name: Applicability
defs.docs: Whether a suggestion can be safely applied.

defs.name: Artifact
defs.value: Artifact { package_id, target, profile, features, filenames, fresh }
defs.docs: A compiler-generated file.

defs.name: package_id
defs.docs: The workspace member this artifact belongs to

defs.name: target
defs.docs: The target this artifact was compiled for

defs.name: profile
defs.docs: The profile this artifact was compiled with

defs.name: features
defs.docs: The enabled features for this artifact

defs.name: filenames
defs.docs: The full paths to the generated artifacts

defs.name: fresh
defs.docs: If true, then the files were already generated

defs.name: Target
defs.value: Target { name, kind, crate_types, required_features, src_path, edition }
defs.docs: A single target (lib, bin, example, ...) provided by a crate

defs.name: name
defs.docs: Name as given in the `Cargo.toml` or generated from the file name

defs.name: kind
defs.docs: Kind of target ("bin", "example", "test", "bench", "lib")

defs.name: crate_types
defs.docs:
Almost the same as `kind`, except when an example is a library instad of an executable.
 In that case `crate_types` contains things like `rlib` and `dylib` while `kind` is `example`

defs.name: required_features
defs.docs:
This target is built only if these features are enabled.
 It doesn't apply to `lib` targets.

defs.name: src_path
defs.docs: Path to the main source file of the target

defs.name: edition
defs.docs: Rust edition for this target

defs.name: WorkspaceMember
defs.docs:
A workspace member. This is basically identical to `cargo::core::package_id::PackageId`, except
 that this does not use `Arc` internally.

defs.name: ArtifactProfile
defs.value: ArtifactProfile { opt_level, debuginfo, debug_assertions, overflow_checks, test }
defs.docs:
Profile settings used to determine which compiler flags to use for a
 target.

defs.name: opt_level
defs.docs: Optimization level. Possible values are 0-3, s or z.

defs.name: debuginfo
defs.docs: The amount of debug info. 0 for none, 1 for limited, 2 for full

defs.name: debug_assertions
defs.docs:
State of the `cfg(debug_assertions)` directive, enabling macros like
 `debug_assert!`

defs.name: overflow_checks
defs.docs: State of the overflow checks.

defs.name: test
defs.docs: Whether this profile is a test

defs.name: FromCompiler
defs.docs: Message left by the compiler

defs.name: package_id
defs.docs: The workspace member this message belongs to

defs.name: target
defs.docs: The target this message is aimed at

defs.name: message
defs.docs: The message the compiler sent.

defs.docs: The workspace member this build script execution belongs to

defs.name: linked_libs
defs.docs: The libs to link

defs.name: linked_paths
defs.docs: The paths to search when resolving libs

defs.name: cfgs
defs.docs: The paths to search when resolving libs

defs.name: env
defs.docs: The environment variables to add to the compilation
